1
00:00:00,933 --> 00:00:03,000
<i>It broke my heart
when you stood me up</i>

2
00:00:03,133 --> 00:00:04,000
<i> because of how I looked.</i>

3
00:00:04,133 --> 00:00:05,867
<i>If looks were all
that mattered to me,</i>

4
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:07,967
<i>I wouldn't have said
"yes" at prom.</i>

5
00:00:08,100 --> 00:00:09,867
<i>It's what's inside
that matters.</i>

6
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:12,500
<i>We need to get in there
to find Juan.</i>

7
00:00:12,633 --> 00:00:14,067
<i>But not by pretending
to be someone else.</i>

8
00:00:14,200 --> 00:00:17,100
<i>Don't put yourself at risk,
Cheska.</i>

9
00:00:17,233 --> 00:00:18,567
<i> Okay?</i>

10
00:00:18,700 --> 00:00:20,500
<i>Did Leon say
he's on his way home?</i>

11
00:00:20,633 --> 00:00:21,533
<i> Not yet.</i>

12
00:00:21,667 --> 00:00:23,500
<i> Keep a close eye on him.</i>

13
00:00:23,633 --> 00:00:25,400
<i>We'll get the truth
out of Leon eventually.</i>

14
00:00:25,533 --> 00:00:26,833
<i> Can we just stay here?</i>

15
00:00:26,967 --> 00:00:28,733
<i>I have a whole new life,
Gio.</i>

16
00:00:28,867 --> 00:00:30,267
<i> I'm no longer Solenn.</i>

17
00:00:30,400 --> 00:00:32,133
<i> I have a family to look after.</i>

18
00:00:32,267 --> 00:00:33,567
<i> I made a promise to Dad.</i>

19
00:00:38,833 --> 00:00:45,867
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

20
00:00:48,500 --> 00:00:49,600
Good night.

21
00:00:50,367 --> 00:00:51,233
Good night.

22
00:00:52,933 --> 00:00:59,933
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

23
00:01:11,533 --> 00:01:18,567
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

24
00:02:12,567 --> 00:02:14,367
- Bro.
- Yes, bro?

25
00:02:16,300 --> 00:02:17,300
Ice cream? Really?

26
00:02:17,433 --> 00:02:18,833
I brushed my teeth already.

27
00:02:19,900 --> 00:02:22,600
It's your favorite flavor, bro.

28
00:02:22,733 --> 00:02:26,467
It has marshmallows,
nuts, and chocolate.

29
00:02:26,600 --> 00:02:28,233
It's Double Dutch, bro.

30
00:02:28,367 --> 00:02:29,967
That's Mama's favorite flavor.

31
00:02:30,100 --> 00:02:32,233
She eats that
after every breakup.

32
00:02:35,333 --> 00:02:36,867
Bro...

33
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:38,333
Are you going through
a breakup?

34
00:02:39,533 --> 00:02:41,067
Who broke your heart?

35
00:02:41,200 --> 00:02:43,333
[HUFFS] Bro,
I'm not broken-hearted.

36
00:02:43,467 --> 00:02:44,633
I'm fine.

37
00:02:45,433 --> 00:02:46,400
You're not.

38
00:02:49,667 --> 00:02:51,333
I know you're hurting.

39
00:02:51,467 --> 00:02:52,667
Huh? Me?

40
00:02:56,633 --> 00:02:58,467
Look, Kiko,

41
00:02:58,600 --> 00:03:00,967
I'll get into
the details later,

42
00:03:01,100 --> 00:03:03,100
but this is the important part.

43
00:03:04,733 --> 00:03:07,033
I know you've already
made a decision,

44
00:03:07,167 --> 00:03:08,733
- but you should know this.
- Geez, Cheska.

45
00:03:08,867 --> 00:03:11,233
Just spit it out.

46
00:03:11,367 --> 00:03:13,033
Okay, fine. Here it is.

47
00:03:14,733 --> 00:03:17,967
I was at Jade's house today.

48
00:03:18,100 --> 00:03:20,067
What were you doing there?

49
00:03:22,167 --> 00:03:24,000
Because, um...

50
00:03:24,133 --> 00:03:28,467
Trixie and I spoke to
Justin about the bar.

51
00:03:28,600 --> 00:03:30,233
- Mm.
- That's why I went there.

52
00:03:30,367 --> 00:03:31,433
Okay, alright.

53
00:03:33,367 --> 00:03:35,367
And then, what?

54
00:03:41,600 --> 00:03:44,067
I saw her with Edward.

55
00:03:46,600 --> 00:03:48,300
They were so close, bro.

56
00:03:49,567 --> 00:03:51,733
I know they're close.

57
00:03:51,867 --> 00:03:53,567
I'm telling you, bro.

58
00:03:53,700 --> 00:03:55,067
They were really, really close.

59
00:03:57,867 --> 00:04:00,200
They were practically
making out.

60
00:04:02,167 --> 00:04:07,167
Jade did mention that
Edward's courting her.

61
00:04:08,433 --> 00:04:09,533
Really?

62
00:04:10,367 --> 00:04:13,733
Don't tell anyone.
But yeah, she told me.

63
00:04:14,833 --> 00:04:16,733
And you're okay with that?

64
00:04:18,767 --> 00:04:21,533
Of course.
Why wouldn't I be?

65
00:04:21,667 --> 00:04:24,100
As long as
my best friend's happy.

66
00:04:25,667 --> 00:04:28,167
Are you sure
you don't need this?

67
00:04:29,300 --> 00:04:30,367
I'm fine.

68
00:04:32,233 --> 00:04:33,400
If you say so.

69
00:04:34,500 --> 00:04:36,967
This does look good though...

70
00:04:37,800 --> 00:04:39,700
Fine, give it to me then.

71
00:04:39,833 --> 00:04:41,033
Go rest already.

72
00:04:41,767 --> 00:04:44,267
- You sure?
- Mm-hmm. Thank you.

73
00:04:45,767 --> 00:04:48,633
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

74
00:04:48,767 --> 00:04:50,800
- Night, brother.
- Night.

75
00:04:50,933 --> 00:04:57,933
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

76
00:05:00,167 --> 00:05:02,100
Stick to what you said.

77
00:05:04,667 --> 00:05:06,700
You're better off as friends.

78
00:05:06,833 --> 00:05:13,867
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

79
00:05:29,100 --> 00:05:36,100
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

80
00:05:43,067 --> 00:05:44,800
I've spoken to Leon.

81
00:05:44,933 --> 00:05:48,033
He said that
if we had to choose between

82
00:05:48,167 --> 00:05:51,000
Uncle Ronald and
Andy Arellano as hotel partner,

83
00:05:51,133 --> 00:05:52,900
we should put it to a vote.

84
00:05:53,033 --> 00:05:54,967
He assured me that this time,

85
00:05:55,100 --> 00:05:57,300
he will vote for Uncle Ronald.

86
00:05:57,433 --> 00:06:00,333
Won't Luna have
a problem with that?

87
00:06:00,467 --> 00:06:02,800
Well, that's what
I was thinking too.

88
00:06:03,533 --> 00:06:06,133
I mean, as much as I want us
to get Uncle Ronald,

89
00:06:06,267 --> 00:06:08,733
it might just cause us
problems internally.

90
00:06:08,900 --> 00:06:11,133
Then let's choose
Andy to save us the trouble.

91
00:06:11,267 --> 00:06:13,500
Luna said the guy's okay.

92
00:06:13,633 --> 00:06:16,967
[MARTIN] But Uncle Ronald
is the better choice, Gio.

93
00:06:18,233 --> 00:06:20,233
Let's not complicate things.

94
00:06:20,967 --> 00:06:22,633
Actually...

95
00:06:22,767 --> 00:06:24,967
Leon doesn't like Andy.

96
00:06:25,100 --> 00:06:27,033
You convinced him again,
didn't you?

97
00:06:27,167 --> 00:06:28,200
No.

98
00:06:28,333 --> 00:06:31,367
He said himself that
he's against Andy.

99
00:06:31,500 --> 00:06:33,767
So if one of them
doesn't trust Andy,

100
00:06:33,900 --> 00:06:36,000
shouldn't we take that
into consideration?

101
00:06:36,833 --> 00:06:39,333
Look,
if Luna's okay with Andy,

102
00:06:39,467 --> 00:06:41,267
then why shouldn't
we be on board, too?

103
00:06:41,433 --> 00:06:42,633
Why are you on
her side now?

104
00:06:42,767 --> 00:06:44,167
Wait a minute, guys.

105
00:06:44,300 --> 00:06:45,433
Chill out!

106
00:06:45,567 --> 00:06:47,133
We don't want the Almazans
fighting over this.

107
00:06:47,267 --> 00:06:48,633
So we shouldn't be
arguing either.

108
00:06:48,767 --> 00:06:55,600
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

109
00:06:58,567 --> 00:07:00,867
Did Leon not respond
to your message last night?

110
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:02,933
No.
He left my message on read.

111
00:07:03,067 --> 00:07:04,467
Didn't he have
security with him?

112
00:07:04,600 --> 00:07:06,633
Joe said he didn't.

113
00:07:07,900 --> 00:07:09,933
Or maybe
he's at the hotel?

114
00:07:10,067 --> 00:07:12,467
Maybe he was too tired
to come home.

115
00:07:12,600 --> 00:07:14,000
I'll call the hotel.

116
00:07:14,167 --> 00:07:15,600
Call Leon's phone.

117
00:07:15,733 --> 00:07:17,000
Yes, Luna.

118
00:07:18,533 --> 00:07:22,633
[LINE RINGING]

119
00:07:25,733 --> 00:07:26,933
[PHONE RINGS]

120
00:07:27,700 --> 00:07:28,533
Hello.

121
00:07:29,533 --> 00:07:30,667
Good morning.

122
00:07:30,800 --> 00:07:32,267
Is my brother at the hotel?

123
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:34,533
You mean Leon?

124
00:07:35,633 --> 00:07:37,533
Leon's not here.

125
00:07:39,467 --> 00:07:41,667
He isn't here.
Is something wrong?

126
00:07:42,700 --> 00:07:44,267
He didn't come home last night.

127
00:07:46,700 --> 00:07:47,967
I'll call you later.

128
00:07:52,367 --> 00:07:53,600
Okay, bye.

129
00:07:55,567 --> 00:07:56,433
[PHONE BEEPS]

130
00:07:56,567 --> 00:07:57,733
Was that Luna?

131
00:07:57,867 --> 00:08:01,267
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

132
00:08:01,400 --> 00:08:02,800
Yes.

133
00:08:03,733 --> 00:08:05,067
She's looking for Leon.
He didn't come home last night.

134
00:08:05,200 --> 00:08:08,600
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

135
00:08:08,733 --> 00:08:09,667
He's not at the hotel.

136
00:08:09,800 --> 00:08:11,233
I can't reach him either.

137
00:08:11,367 --> 00:08:18,400
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

138
00:08:19,867 --> 00:08:21,133
Why would she call you?

139
00:08:22,100 --> 00:08:23,567
So what if she called me?

140
00:08:23,700 --> 00:08:26,533
She could've called
the front desk to ask.

141
00:08:27,400 --> 00:08:29,133
So what if
she called me instead?

142
00:08:29,267 --> 00:08:36,167
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

143
00:08:36,300 --> 00:08:38,167
Gio and Luna are talking?

144
00:08:40,133 --> 00:08:41,567
I wonder where Leon is.

145
00:08:41,700 --> 00:08:48,500
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

146
00:08:53,433 --> 00:08:54,767
- Raphie!
- Sir Leon hasn't texted

147
00:08:54,800 --> 00:08:56,133
or called.

148
00:08:56,133 --> 00:08:57,233
Talk to the boatmen!

149
00:08:57,233 --> 00:08:58,967
They might have seen
Leon yesterday.

150
00:08:58,967 --> 00:09:02,133
Luna, maybe we need
to report it to the police?

151
00:09:02,133 --> 00:09:03,900
Jade. Luna.

152
00:09:04,700 --> 00:09:06,867
Have you heard from Leon?

153
00:09:06,867 --> 00:09:08,767
Not yet, but his phone
was ringing.

154
00:09:08,767 --> 00:09:10,600
I also had Joe trace him

155
00:09:10,600 --> 00:09:11,900
If he doesn't answer tomorrow,

156
00:09:11,900 --> 00:09:14,533
we might have
to report it to the police.

157
00:09:14,533 --> 00:09:16,000
Alright, Miss Luna.

158
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:17,833
I will talk to
the boatmen first.

159
00:09:18,733 --> 00:09:21,767
- I'll go with you, Raphie.
- Alright. Excuse us.

160
00:09:21,767 --> 00:09:23,900
- Be careful.
- Alright, thank you.

161
00:09:23,900 --> 00:09:30,833
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

162
00:09:33,800 --> 00:09:36,067
Thanks, Banks.
Keep us posted, okay?

163
00:09:36,900 --> 00:09:39,100
Thank you. Take care.

164
00:09:40,033 --> 00:09:42,500
[SIGHS] Let's stay positive.

165
00:09:42,500 --> 00:09:45,133
[INHALES] Nothing bad
has happened to Sir Leon.

166
00:09:45,133 --> 00:09:47,700
Maybe... he just visited
his friend.

167
00:09:48,933 --> 00:09:51,667
Or maybe he just wanted
to eat beef stew!

168
00:09:51,667 --> 00:09:54,667
It was so good, he forgot
to message his sibling!

169
00:09:54,667 --> 00:09:55,900
That's the scenario.

170
00:09:57,767 --> 00:09:59,600
Then, alright...

171
00:09:59,600 --> 00:10:02,600
to reduce the
stress in your body...

172
00:10:02,633 --> 00:10:04,133
how are you
and Mr. Edward?

173
00:10:04,133 --> 00:10:06,267
Any updates?

174
00:10:06,267 --> 00:10:08,567
I was just asking
for an update!

175
00:10:08,567 --> 00:10:10,167
How about this then.

176
00:10:10,167 --> 00:10:12,233
Have you confessed yet?

177
00:10:17,567 --> 00:10:18,833
[GASPS]

178
00:10:20,033 --> 00:10:21,700
Does Sir Kiko know?

179
00:10:22,533 --> 00:10:24,967
- He knows.
- [GASPS]

180
00:10:24,967 --> 00:10:26,633
What did he say?

181
00:10:26,633 --> 00:10:28,800
He told me...

182
00:10:28,800 --> 00:10:31,667
if i'm happy, then he's happy

183
00:10:31,667 --> 00:10:33,233
[GASPS]

184
00:10:33,233 --> 00:10:35,300
So... so what will happen?

185
00:10:35,333 --> 00:10:38,167
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

186
00:10:38,167 --> 00:10:39,867
I don't know, Raphie!

187
00:10:39,867 --> 00:10:42,600
I'm just so confused!

188
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:44,167
All I know is...

189
00:10:44,167 --> 00:10:45,867
when I was with Edward...

190
00:10:47,200 --> 00:10:50,167
- we had a moment
- [GASPS, COUGHS]

191
00:10:51,300 --> 00:10:52,867
You kissed?

192
00:10:52,867 --> 00:10:54,333
Kissed? No!

193
00:10:54,333 --> 00:10:56,000
What do you mean, no!

194
00:10:56,000 --> 00:10:58,900
No! We didn't kiss!
I mean, it was close.

195
00:10:58,900 --> 00:11:00,167
But it didn't happen.

196
00:11:00,167 --> 00:11:02,800
But you didn't stop it!
You didn't fight it!

197
00:11:04,133 --> 00:11:06,267
Oh, my gosh.

198
00:11:06,267 --> 00:11:08,267
It's the feelings that matters!

199
00:11:08,300 --> 00:11:09,833
Ladies and gentlemen,

200
00:11:09,833 --> 00:11:12,233
and everything in between,
under the ocean...

201
00:11:12,233 --> 00:11:14,267
we have a situationship.

202
00:11:14,267 --> 00:11:16,900
Situationship? What is that?

203
00:11:16,900 --> 00:11:18,600
Situationship.

204
00:11:18,600 --> 00:11:21,900
You guys don't have a label.
You're not even 'MU'...

205
00:11:21,900 --> 00:11:24,167
because you never told
him you liked him, right?

206
00:11:25,267 --> 00:11:26,667
Hey! So...

207
00:11:26,667 --> 00:11:29,367
There are no mutual feelings
or mutual understanding...

208
00:11:29,367 --> 00:11:31,167
that you want each other.

209
00:11:31,167 --> 00:11:32,967
[SIGHS] Listen.

210
00:11:32,967 --> 00:11:34,300
Trust your gut.

211
00:11:35,133 --> 00:11:36,900
The what?

212
00:11:38,333 --> 00:11:39,800
Close your eyes.

213
00:11:40,333 --> 00:11:42,300
- I did this last night.
- Shh!

214
00:11:43,067 --> 00:11:44,367
I'm not done yet.

215
00:11:45,300 --> 00:11:46,733
Miss Jade?

216
00:11:47,067 --> 00:11:48,633
Feel it.

217
00:11:48,633 --> 00:11:50,200
Feel? What should I feel?

218
00:11:50,200 --> 00:11:52,733
Shh! Come on.
Close your eyes. Feel it.

219
00:11:53,833 --> 00:11:55,200
[SIGHS]

220
00:11:55,200 --> 00:11:56,833
Are you confused?

221
00:11:57,733 --> 00:12:01,667
Are you more than friends
but less than lovers?

222
00:12:03,233 --> 00:12:07,267
If yes, that's situationship.

223
00:12:07,267 --> 00:12:14,233
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

224
00:12:19,200 --> 00:12:21,967
That's where my grandfather
and grandmother started.

225
00:12:27,067 --> 00:12:34,000
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

226
00:12:35,367 --> 00:12:39,100
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

227
00:12:39,100 --> 00:12:40,367
[SIGHS]

228
00:12:49,367 --> 00:12:51,000
I'm here.

229
00:12:51,300 --> 00:12:53,033
You were looking for me, right?

230
00:12:54,933 --> 00:12:56,367
Gio!

231
00:12:57,067 --> 00:12:58,967
Someone might see us!

232
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:01,400
There's no one here.

233
00:13:07,000 --> 00:13:08,933
I know you're worried
about Leon.

234
00:13:09,700 --> 00:13:10,900
Me too.

235
00:13:10,900 --> 00:13:17,100
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

236
00:13:17,100 --> 00:13:19,100
Nothing bad will happen
to him, okay?

237
00:13:20,767 --> 00:13:22,133
I hope so.

238
00:13:22,167 --> 00:13:29,100
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

239
00:13:36,133 --> 00:13:38,000
It's Andy.

240
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:39,500
Andy Arellano.

241
00:13:39,500 --> 00:13:41,300
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

242
00:13:41,300 --> 00:13:43,067
Are you sure?

243
00:13:43,067 --> 00:13:44,933
Isn't he a family friend
of yours?

244
00:13:46,067 --> 00:13:48,300
[HENRI] If it's Arellano,

245
00:13:48,300 --> 00:13:50,000
why would he do it?

246
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:51,867
Did you have a disagreement?

247
00:13:51,867 --> 00:13:53,133
A little.

248
00:13:53,867 --> 00:13:55,000
A little?

249
00:13:55,467 --> 00:13:58,767
Leon, you need
to be more specific.

250
00:13:59,767 --> 00:14:04,200
We argued because I didn't
agree to be partners.

251
00:14:05,133 --> 00:14:09,100
We had a confrontation
and things got heated.

252
00:14:09,833 --> 00:14:11,900
Did it lead to physical
violence?

253
00:14:11,900 --> 00:14:14,233
Or did he threaten you?

254
00:14:15,267 --> 00:14:19,367
It would be helpful if there's
a text message as evidence.

255
00:14:19,367 --> 00:14:22,867
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

256
00:14:22,867 --> 00:14:24,433
There's nothing.

257
00:14:25,367 --> 00:14:27,400
That's gonna be a problem.

258
00:14:29,067 --> 00:14:30,967
All I'm saying is,

259
00:14:30,967 --> 00:14:32,433
if anything happens to me,

260
00:14:32,433 --> 00:14:34,233
you know who's responsible.

261
00:14:34,233 --> 00:14:41,167
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

262
00:14:44,467 --> 00:14:47,533
[PHONE VIBRATING]

263
00:14:47,533 --> 00:14:48,467
Leon?

264
00:14:49,500 --> 00:14:50,733
[LEON] We need to meet.

265
00:14:50,967 --> 00:14:52,133
Where are you?

266
00:14:52,133 --> 00:14:54,067
Your siblings have been
looking for you.

267
00:14:55,033 --> 00:14:56,767
Martin, let's meet right now.

268
00:14:57,033 --> 00:14:58,033
It's urgent.

269
00:14:58,533 --> 00:14:59,867
Not at the hotel.

270
00:14:59,867 --> 00:15:01,067
I'll send you the location.

271
00:15:03,633 --> 00:15:04,700
Alright.

272
00:15:04,700 --> 00:15:06,100
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

273
00:15:06,100 --> 00:15:07,133
Huh?

274
00:15:07,600 --> 00:15:08,867
You're on your way here?

275
00:15:09,500 --> 00:15:10,533
Oh...

276
00:15:10,533 --> 00:15:13,700
[STUTTERING] Okay, I'll--
I'll inform Martin.

277
00:15:16,800 --> 00:15:18,633
Uh, did you see Sir...

278
00:15:18,633 --> 00:15:20,600
- Sir Martin?
- Oh, he just left.

279
00:15:22,533 --> 00:15:24,000
Did he say where he
was going to?

280
00:15:24,733 --> 00:15:27,133
He didn't mention where
but he just left just now.

281
00:15:27,600 --> 00:15:28,833
Looks like he's in a hurry.

282
00:15:32,500 --> 00:15:33,533
[CLICKS TONGUE]

283
00:15:33,733 --> 00:15:36,167
[PHONE RINGING]

284
00:15:36,200 --> 00:15:43,200
[CAR ENGINE REVVING]

285
00:15:43,200 --> 00:15:50,133
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

286
00:15:59,500 --> 00:16:00,733
[CAR DOOR OPENS]

287
00:16:05,133 --> 00:16:06,400
[CAR DOOR CLOSES]

288
00:16:17,167 --> 00:16:18,533
[MARTIN] Bro...

289
00:16:19,933 --> 00:16:21,567
what the hell?

290
00:16:21,567 --> 00:16:28,500
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

291
00:16:32,967 --> 00:16:34,967
Hold on. What is this place?!

292
00:16:36,033 --> 00:16:37,733
Why did you bring me here?

293
00:16:43,667 --> 00:16:44,967
How are my siblings?

294
00:16:45,167 --> 00:16:47,600
Worried about you, of course.
You've gone silent.

295
00:16:48,000 --> 00:16:49,267
And they'll grown
even more worried

296
00:16:49,267 --> 00:16:50,900
if they see
your state right now.

297
00:16:51,933 --> 00:16:53,067
I know them.

298
00:16:54,200 --> 00:16:55,567
If I call them right now,

299
00:16:55,800 --> 00:16:57,700
they won't stop pestering
me with questions.

300
00:16:59,133 --> 00:17:02,600
[PHONE VIBRATING, BEEPS]

301
00:17:03,733 --> 00:17:05,800
Just what is going on, Leon?

302
00:17:08,933 --> 00:17:09,967
It's Uncle Andy.

303
00:17:11,533 --> 00:17:13,633
This is done by one of his men.

304
00:17:13,833 --> 00:17:14,833
But why?

305
00:17:15,133 --> 00:17:16,567
Did he find out you didn't
want him

306
00:17:16,567 --> 00:17:17,800
to be a business partner
at the hotel?

307
00:17:19,000 --> 00:17:20,033
No.

308
00:17:21,833 --> 00:17:23,033
It's because
of a different reason.

309
00:17:23,033 --> 00:17:24,767
[HUFFS] Bro!

310
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:27,000
Just one call
and I'll be there!

311
00:17:27,300 --> 00:17:30,167
You owe me an explanation
on what is really going on!

312
00:17:32,033 --> 00:17:34,733
What is going on, Leon?!

313
00:17:34,733 --> 00:17:38,733
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING, FADES]

314
00:17:42,600 --> 00:17:44,567
Uh... Ms. Jade?

315
00:17:44,567 --> 00:17:47,667
Ms. Jade, is it alright
if take over for the meantime?

316
00:17:48,167 --> 00:17:51,600
I'll just talk to the other
boatmen that I know.

317
00:17:51,600 --> 00:17:53,100
Sure thing. It's for Martin.

318
00:17:53,100 --> 00:17:55,200
Go ahead, Raphie. Thank you.
I'll take over from here.

319
00:17:55,200 --> 00:17:57,133
- Thank you, Ms. Jade.
- Thank you, Raphie.

320
00:17:58,633 --> 00:17:59,700
[SIGHS]

321
00:18:01,033 --> 00:18:04,833
[PAPERS FLAPPING, RUSTLING]

322
00:18:04,833 --> 00:18:08,133
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

323
00:18:08,133 --> 00:18:09,567
[JADE] Oh, sir!

324
00:18:09,567 --> 00:18:10,567
Hello, sir!

325
00:18:10,567 --> 00:18:12,133
Welcome to Hotel 88!

326
00:18:12,567 --> 00:18:14,967
Do you have a reservation, sir?

327
00:18:14,967 --> 00:18:17,200
Oh, no, no. I'm here to speak
to Martin.

328
00:18:17,600 --> 00:18:18,633
Is he around?

329
00:18:18,633 --> 00:18:20,700
Oh... Martin?

330
00:18:20,700 --> 00:18:21,700
Yes.

331
00:18:22,200 --> 00:18:23,200
Um...

332
00:18:24,633 --> 00:18:26,067
Oh, perfect. Kiko!

333
00:18:26,267 --> 00:18:27,500
Hmm?

334
00:18:27,500 --> 00:18:30,833
Sir, this is Kiko. He's
a brother of Martin.

335
00:18:31,200 --> 00:18:32,567
Do you know where Martin is?

336
00:18:33,067 --> 00:18:34,200
Is he around?

337
00:18:34,200 --> 00:18:36,333
I told them
that I'd be coming by.

338
00:18:37,300 --> 00:18:39,033
Oh, is that so, sir?

339
00:18:39,867 --> 00:18:42,200
He just left for a bit
but he'll come back soon.

340
00:18:42,733 --> 00:18:44,800
Ah... How about his girlfriend?

341
00:18:44,800 --> 00:18:45,867
Is she here?

342
00:18:46,100 --> 00:18:48,100
Uh... girlfriend?

343
00:18:49,033 --> 00:18:52,033
[LAUGHS] Sir, Martin
doesn't have a girlfriend.

344
00:18:52,033 --> 00:18:56,233
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

345
00:18:56,267 --> 00:18:58,167
Are you really
Martin's brother?

346
00:18:59,833 --> 00:19:02,667
Why don't you know about
your brother's personal life?

347
00:19:03,867 --> 00:19:07,033
Kiko, maybe we should
ask Sari first?

348
00:19:07,233 --> 00:19:09,667
Uh, yes. Sari is indeed
who I'm looking for.

349
00:19:09,667 --> 00:19:10,633
Is she here?

350
00:19:10,633 --> 00:19:13,767
Oh, apologies... you said
girlfriend, so...

351
00:19:14,167 --> 00:19:15,133
Yes!

352
00:19:15,133 --> 00:19:17,033
Sari is Martin's girlfriend.

353
00:19:17,833 --> 00:19:19,700
Sir, I'm sorry, but...

354
00:19:19,900 --> 00:19:22,400
Sari is Martin's executive
assistant,

355
00:19:22,400 --> 00:19:23,933
not girlfriend.

356
00:19:25,833 --> 00:19:26,833
What?

357
00:19:31,300 --> 00:19:32,700
Are you serious?

358
00:19:32,700 --> 00:19:39,667
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

359
00:19:44,100 --> 00:19:45,367
- Sir...
- Sir!

360
00:19:57,633 --> 00:20:03,033
[LEON PANTING]

361
00:20:03,200 --> 00:20:04,867
Bro, just what
are we doing here?!

362
00:20:05,900 --> 00:20:06,933
Huh?

363
00:20:07,067 --> 00:20:09,067
What's going on here? Tell me!

364
00:20:09,200 --> 00:20:11,300
What, why, when, how, who?!

365
00:20:11,433 --> 00:20:13,433
Leon! I need to know!
Give me something!

366
00:20:13,567 --> 00:20:15,333
- Give me everything!
- It's here!

367
00:20:17,067 --> 00:20:18,200
It's right at this spot!

368
00:20:18,333 --> 00:20:20,433
- What is?!
- I hit him!

369
00:20:21,567 --> 00:20:24,200
[SOBBING] I killed him here!
Right at this spot!

370
00:20:25,433 --> 00:20:26,967
What? What do you--

371
00:20:27,100 --> 00:20:29,467
- I killed someone, Martin.
- What are you saying?

372
00:20:30,033 --> 00:20:31,967
You hit-- killed someone,
who did?

373
00:20:32,967 --> 00:20:33,867
You?

374
00:20:34,433 --> 00:20:35,667
I killed someone...

375
00:20:36,933 --> 00:20:38,300
I killed someone!

376
00:20:39,500 --> 00:20:40,800
I killed someone!

377
00:20:42,933 --> 00:20:44,267
Leon! Leon!

378
00:20:44,400 --> 00:20:47,000
- Okay, okay, okay...
- [LEON PANTING]

379
00:20:47,367 --> 00:20:48,600
Who is he?

380
00:20:49,433 --> 00:20:50,733
Do we know him?

381
00:20:52,333 --> 00:20:53,967
- Based on the investigation...
- [HUFFS]

382
00:20:54,100 --> 00:20:55,200
You're investigating?!

383
00:20:55,333 --> 00:20:57,300
I am. For a while now.

384
00:20:58,367 --> 00:20:59,700
Some time after dad died.

385
00:21:00,600 --> 00:21:02,300
That's when I started
investigating.

386
00:21:03,367 --> 00:21:04,700
And I learned...

387
00:21:05,167 --> 00:21:07,567
that his name
is Sandro Soliman.

388
00:21:10,800 --> 00:21:11,967
Sandro Soliman...

389
00:21:12,833 --> 00:21:13,800
Who is that?

390
00:21:15,633 --> 00:21:17,700
He is Uncle Mike's
former contractor

391
00:21:17,833 --> 00:21:18,967
in Hotel 88.

392
00:21:22,100 --> 00:21:23,200
I accidentally hit him

393
00:21:23,333 --> 00:21:25,300
two months before Dad died.

394
00:21:26,267 --> 00:21:27,633
And that Sandro guy...

395
00:21:28,567 --> 00:21:30,400
was going to kill my father.

396
00:21:31,533 --> 00:21:33,000
So I killed him
before he could.

397
00:21:34,700 --> 00:21:36,667
And our fathers
know about all of it?

398
00:21:37,933 --> 00:21:39,300
Yes.

399
00:21:40,333 --> 00:21:41,667
That Sandro guy was the one
who set Hotel 88

400
00:21:41,800 --> 00:21:43,033
on fire before.

401
00:21:45,367 --> 00:21:47,133
That's what your father
was investigating on

402
00:21:47,267 --> 00:21:48,433
before he died.

403
00:21:48,567 --> 00:21:55,567
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

404
00:21:57,467 --> 00:21:59,000
I'm sorry, Martin.

405
00:22:02,267 --> 00:22:04,033
Sorry I only told you
about this now.

406
00:22:04,167 --> 00:22:09,433
[LEON PANTING CONTINUES]

407
00:22:09,567 --> 00:22:11,533
[MARTIN BREATHES DEEPLY]

408
00:22:11,667 --> 00:22:12,867
Earlier,

409
00:22:13,167 --> 00:22:14,633
you mentioned
that Andy Arellano

410
00:22:14,800 --> 00:22:16,133
sent one of his men
to beat you up.

411
00:22:16,633 --> 00:22:18,500
And you're so certain about it

412
00:22:18,633 --> 00:22:20,633
so you mean to tell me...

413
00:22:20,767 --> 00:22:22,367
he also has something
to do about this?

414
00:22:23,033 --> 00:22:24,400
Yes.

415
00:22:25,433 --> 00:22:27,633
Because Sandro's phone
is in my possession.

416
00:22:28,200 --> 00:22:29,733
And Andy?

417
00:22:30,367 --> 00:22:32,067
He called on that very phone.

418
00:22:33,367 --> 00:22:34,767
I heard him, Martin.

419
00:22:35,800 --> 00:22:37,000
I heard him.

420
00:22:38,267 --> 00:22:39,833
And he only wanted one thing.

421
00:22:42,367 --> 00:22:45,100
And that is to enter Hotel 88.

422
00:22:46,000 --> 00:22:49,667
What? What...
what are you saying?

423
00:22:50,367 --> 00:22:51,567
Think about it.

424
00:22:52,800 --> 00:22:55,033
If Uncle Andy is connected
to Sandro,

425
00:22:55,167 --> 00:22:57,300
it's not impossible that he has
something to do

426
00:22:57,433 --> 00:23:01,033
with the death of my dad
and your father

427
00:23:01,700 --> 00:23:04,000
just to acquire Hotel 88.

428
00:23:04,133 --> 00:23:11,000
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

429
00:23:18,600 --> 00:23:20,100
<i>You shouldn't tell this
to anybody.</i>

430
00:23:20,233 --> 00:23:22,633
<i>Neither my siblings
nor yours.</i>

431
00:23:22,800 --> 00:23:24,400
<i> They can't know about this.</i>

432
00:23:24,533 --> 00:23:25,667
<i> Our focus right now</i>

433
00:23:25,800 --> 00:23:27,833
<i>is to keep Andy from becoming
part of the hotel.</i>

434
00:23:27,967 --> 00:23:30,333
<i>It's the only way
to protect our families.</i>

435
00:23:30,467 --> 00:23:32,433
<i>You let your friend
trick you, Leon?</i>

436
00:23:32,567 --> 00:23:34,267
<i>If I say that it's not
Uncle Andy,</i>

437
00:23:34,400 --> 00:23:35,633
<i> it's not Uncle Andy!</i>

438
00:23:35,767 --> 00:23:37,633
<i>If I can't get through
them legally,</i>

439
00:23:37,767 --> 00:23:38,800
<i>I'll have to pressure them
some other way.</i>

440
00:23:38,933 --> 00:23:40,900
<i>Looks like you have
a problem with Sir Ronald.</i>

441
00:23:41,033 --> 00:23:42,133
<i> We're all in danger.</i>

442
00:23:42,267 --> 00:23:43,400
<i> We have to act before he does.</i>

443
00:23:43,533 --> 00:23:44,367
[SCREAMING IN PAIN]

444
00:23:44,500 --> 00:23:45,900
<i> Where's the map?</i>

445
00:23:46,033 --> 00:23:47,100
<i> Where's the map?!</i>
